Enum TestState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TestState>
      • com.undercamber.TestState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TestState>

    public enum TestState
extends java.lang.Enum<TestState>
    Indicates the stage in a test's lifecycle.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      COMPLETE_FAILED
      The test ran to completion with errors
      COMPLETE_SUCCEEDED
      The test ran to completion without errors
      INITIALIZED
      The test has called TestManager.initialize(com.undercamber.Requirement...), and is awaiting execution.
      NOT_RUN
      The test was not run
      RUNNING_SUBTESTS
      The test has completed execution, and is awaiting completion of its subtests.
      SKIPPED_BY_USER
      The test was skipped because the user did not select it.
      SKIPPED_DUE_TO_PARENT_ERROR
      The test was not run because an ancestor failed
      SKIPPED_DUE_TO_PREREQUISITE_ERROR
      The test was not run because a prerequisite failed
      SKIPPED_DUE_TO_SIBLING_ERROR
      The test was skipped because the subtest mode was SubtestSequencingMode.SEQUENTIAL_ABORT_SEQUENCE_ON_ERROR and a prior sibling failed
      UNINITIALIZED
      The test never called TestManager.initialize(com.undercamber.Requirement...)
